Key Match Events: Ireland secured a five-run win on the Duckworth-Lewis-Stern method when the match was called off due to rain.
England were 105-5 in the 15th over when rain arrived.
Moeen Ali struck 12 in three balls just before the rain came.
England suffered a top-order collapse, slipping to 86-5.
Ireland raced to 102-1 off 12 overs before collapsing to 9-54, being dismissed in the final over.
Post-Match Reflections: England's performance was below-par with both bat and ball.
England's tactics with the bat were curious, struggling to find any timing and hitting only eight boundaries in 87 balls.
England's hopes of a second T20 world title are in real jeopardy.
Friday’s encounter against Australia is effectively a knockout game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was rain-affected, leading to the use of the Duckworth-Lewis-Stern method.
Ireland previously beat England in the 50-over World Cup of 2011.
Wednesday’s later game between New Zealand and Afghanistan at the MCG was abandoned without a ball being bowled because of rain.
